The function [`toLowerCase()`](https://processing.org/reference/String_toLowerCase_.html) and [`toUpperCase()`](https://processing.org/reference/String_toUpperCase_.html) are methods of the class [`String`](https://processing.org/reference/String.html),. This methods do not change characters in place, but return a new string.

Create a new string letter by letter:

```java
String newString = new String();
for(int i=0; i &lt; originalText.length(); i++) {
  
   if (Character.isUpperCase(originalText.charAt(i))) {
       newString += originalText.substring(i, i+1).toLowerCase();
   } else {
       newString += originalText.substring(i, i+1).toUpperCase();
   }
}
```

Or alternatively

```java
String newString = new String();
for(int i=0; i &lt; originalText.length(); i++) {
  
   char ch = originalText.charAt(i);
   if (Character.isUpperCase(ch)) {
       newString += Character.toLowerCase(ch);
   } else {
       newString += Character.toUpperCase(ch);
   } 
}
```

